I think I have sourced TJ's Deism enough at least for my own satisfaction, if not for yours, but I will add that the following words appear in Volume 3 of Dumas Malone's rightfully celebrated biography, "Jefferson and His Time, " with regard to the accusation that Jefferson was an atheist: "... it was not only made in the public press, it was hurled from pulpits in various places, most of all probably in Connecticut.
